    "department": "Product",
    "description": "OVERVIEW\n\nAs a Product Manager at Phia, you’ll drive execution for user-facing product features across the platform. You’ll work closely with Engineering, Design, and Data to define requirements, prioritize work, and ship features from concept through launch and iteration. You’ll be responsible for translating product goals into clear specs, managing day-to-day execution, and using data and user feedback to guide decisions. This role is ideal for someone who enjoys operating close to the build, moving quickly, and delivering measurable product outcomes.\n\n\nABOUT PHIA\n\nPhia is building the AI layer that connects consumers and brands, powering a personalized shopping agent that translates real-time consumer intent into trusted product discovery. Launched in April 2025, Phia has surpassed 1 million users in under a year and partnered with 6,200+ retail brands, representing billions in annual gross merchandise volume. Each month, Phia drives millions of dollars in sales for brands and has achieved 11× revenue growth since launch, with partners seeing higher conversion rates, stronger new customer acquisition, increased average order value, and significantly reduced return rates.\n\nPhia’s core experience is an AI shopping agent embedded directly within users’ natural shopping flow, delivering real-time insights that help users make smarter, more confident purchase decisions.\n\nPhia is a small, high-ownership team building at startup speed. If you want to ship at high velocity, solve complex problems in consumer AI and commerce, and have clear ownership from day one, this is the place to do it.\n\n\nWHAT YOU OWN\n\n - Drive day-to-day execution of product features from requirements through launch\n\n - Write clear product requirements, user stories, and acceptance criteria\n\n - Partner closely with Engineering and Design to scope, prioritize, and deliver work on schedule\n\n - Manage product backlogs, tradeoffs, and iteration plans\n\n - Use data, metrics, and user feedback to evaluate feature performance and inform next steps\n\n - Coordinate launches and communicate updates to cross-functional stakeholders\n\n\nQUALIFICATIONS\n\n - 1–3+ years of experience in product management, product operations, or a related role\n\n - Experience working closely with engineering teams to ship software products\n\n - Strong ability to translate product goals into clear, actionable requirements\n\n - Comfort using data and metrics to support product decisions\n\n - Strong organizational skills and attention to detail in fast-paced environments\n\n - Clear communicator with a bias toward execution and ownership",
